The Portlet Container test portal

  There is the test portal web application to test the portlet container capabilities under
  different application servers

  It is tested to work under <TomCat 5>, <JBoss 4> and <WebLogic 9.1> application servers

  It consists of two .war's:

  * <portal.war> - the test portal itself (a set of filters, listeners, and .jsp's

  * <portlets.war> - two demo portlets

[]

*---*
Deploying under <<WebLogic 9.1, 9.2>>
*---*


  * Copy all necessary .jar's into <%DOMAIN_HOME%\lib> directory

  * Run domain admin server with command <%DOMAIN_HOME%\startWebLogic.cmd>

  * Place <portal.war> and <portlets.war> into random directory (or directories)

  * Run the following command to deploy .war's into server

---------
java weblogic.Deployer -adminurl t3://localhost:7001 -user weblogic -password xxx -deploy C:\path\where\lies\portlets.war
java weblogic.Deployer -adminurl t3://localhost:7001 -user weblogic -password xxx -deploy C:\other\path\where\lies\portal.war
---------

  After that the test portal application will be available at {{http://localhost:7001/portal}}
